HEADWORD: Re-formation
<hw>Re`-for*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(r?`f?r*m?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The act of forming anew; a second forming in order; <as>as, the
<ex>reformation</ex> of a column of troops into a hollow
square</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reformative</ent>⟦br⟧
